    Australia’s Largest Range of 3D Printing Filaments

    Shop Now

    Frequently Asked Questions

    +What can you actually print on a 3D printer?

    Additive manufacturing has opened up a new world for designers, engineers, artists, scientists and marketeers. AM allows users to build parts faster, more accurately, with more freedom and more diverse applications than ever before.

    We are able to provide 3D printer solutions that work for you, 3D printing services with quick turnaround and affordable prices and general advice on 3D printing.

    +How long does it take?
    We operate one of the fastest 3D printers on the market and pride ourselves on quick turnaround times. Specifying your deadline is one of the best ways for us to prioritise your work and deliver for a time suited to you.
    +What does it cost to print a 3D model?

    The price for printed models is based on the amount of time it would take to print the model. Where data may present as unprintable there may be an additional charge for the time spent fixing files. The best way to receive a quote is to email us so that we can identify your requirements.

    How to Request a Quote

    To request a quote for a 3D printed model please attach your CAD file (preferably in .stl format) within an email to thinglab@freedspace.com.au, however if it’s a large file try sending via wetransfer.com. For an accurate quote include the dimensions, scale of the model and the working units. If the print is time sensitive, it’s important to state your deadline.

    +How much does a 3D printer cost?
    3D printers vary greatly in cost (starting at around $2,500) depending on the the technology, build materials available and size. The best way to receive a quote is to contact us so that we can identify your requirements.

    Want To Know More?

    Our team of 3D printing professionals are just an email or a phone call away.
